Name: Apple
Description: The round fruit of a tree of the rose family, which typically has thin green or red skin and crisp flesh.

Name: Dragon Fruit
Description: The fruit of a cactus (= a desert plant with thick stems for storing water) that has bright red or yellow skin and white or red flesh with many small black seeds

Name: Kiwi
Description: A fruit with a thin hairy skin, green flesh, and black seeds.

Name: Parmesan Cheese
Description: Parmesan is an Italian hard, granular cheese produced from cow's milk and aged at least 12 months.

Name: Pineapple
Description: A large, juicy fruit that grows in hotter regions, having a rough skin, a short stem, and pointed leaves on the top, or its sweet, yellow flesh.

Name: Tomato
Description: A glossy red, or occasionally yellow, pulpy edible fruit that is eaten as a vegetable or in salad.

Name: Watermelon
Description: A large oblong or roundish fruit with a hard green or white rind often striped or variegated, a sweet watery pink, yellowish, or red pulp, and usually many seeds.
